+
)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Displays the active SMS Storage Classes
+
!Command Syntax
+ @SCLS class-mask+
+
!Keywords      +
  @class-mask  +An optional masking pattern that can be used to filter the
               +displayed list on all or part of the storage class name.
               +The wildcard character of '*' and a placeholder character of '%'
               +can be used. The default value of class-mask is '*'.
+
!Example
+ @SCLS PROD*+  List all storage classes that start 'PROD'.
+
+When more than one storage class matches the specified pattern mask, a summary
+list is displayed.

!Output Panel Fields
  @Name            +- Storage Class name
  @DRes            +- Direct access response time required (ms)
  @DBia            +- Specification on R/W bias for datasets in this class
  @SRes            +- Sequential access response time required (ms)
  @SBia            +- Specification on R/W bias for datasets in this class
  @Avail           +- How dataset processing continues after device failure
  @Access          +- How Concurrent Copy affects placement of the datasets
  @GSpce           +- Can users pre-allocate space for multi-volume datasets
  @GSW             +- Synchronization for BSAM CHECK and PDS/E WRITE
+
+When only one storage class matches the specified pattern mask, a more detailed
+list is displayed.

!Storage Class Attributes
  @Name            +- Storage Class Name
  @Last Change Date+- The date (yyyy/mm/dd) of the last change
  @Last Change User+- The userid that performed the last change
  @Last Change Time+- The time (hh.mm.ss) of the last change
  @Description     +- Description of the Storage Group
  @Dir-Access Resp +- Direct access response time required (ms)
  @Dir-Access Bias +- Specification on R/W bias for datasets in this class
  @Seq-Access Resp +- Sequential access response time required (ms)
  @Seq-Access Bias +- Specification on R/W bias for datasets in this class
  @Availability    +- How dataset processing continues after device failure
  @Accessibility   +- How Concurrent Copy affects placement of the datasets
  @Guaranteed Space+- Can users pre-allocate space for multi-volume datasets
  @Guaranteed Sync +- Synchronization for BSAM CHECK and PDS/E WRITE
  @Initial Acc Resp+- Time (sec) required to locate/mount/prepare media
  @Data Rate Mb/Sec+- Sequential data transfer rate for striped datasets
+
!CF Cache Set Information
  @Name            +- Name of the CF Cache Set
  @CF Dir Weight   +- Relative importance of Direct Access
  @CF Seq Weight   +- Relative importance of Sequential Access
+
)INIT
.ATTRCHAR(¢)  = 'COLOR(&M7CC) HILITE(&M7CH) INTENS(&M7CI)'
.ATTRCHAR(!)  = 'COLOR(&M08C) HILITE(&M08H) INTENS(&M08I)'
.ATTRCHAR(+)  = 'COLOR(&M06C) HILITE(&M06H) INTENS(&M06I)'
.ATTRCHAR(@)  = 'COLOR(&M09C) HILITE(&M09H) INTENS(&M09I)'
)PROC
 &ZUP   = MXIHTOC
 &ZCONT = MXIHSGRP
)END

MXIHSGRP.text:
)PANEL KEYLIST (ISRHLP2 ISR)
)ATTR
  ¢ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(YELLOW)
  ! TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(WHITE)
  + TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
  @ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
  # AREA(SCRL) EXTEND(ON)
)BODY EXPAND(¯¯) DEFAULT($¦_)
¢MXI - HELP - SGRP Command -----------------------------------------------------
!Option ===>_ZCMD
#MXIHAREA                                                                      #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
+
)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Displays the active SMS Storage Groups
+
!Command Syntax
+ @SGRP grp-mask+
+
!Keywords      +
  @grp-mask    +An optional masking pattern that can be used to filter the
               +displayed list on all or part of the storage group name.
               +The wildcard character of '*' and a placeholder character of '%'
               +can be used. The default value of grp-mask is '*'.
+
!Example
+ @SGRP PROD*+  List all storage groups that start 'PROD'.
+
!Considerations
+The space usage figures reported for storage groups are obtained from SMS via
+a subsystem call. Space usage figures for SMS volumes are only updated when
+a dataset is allocated to the device. Thus it is possible to see zero Mb for
+volume capacity and free space when SMS has yet to allocate a dataset on the
+volume in question on the local system.
+
+For the most accurate and up to date space usage information for a storage
+group, use the@DASD SGRP()+command.
+
!Output Panels
+When more than one storage group matches the specified pattern mask, a summary
+list is displayed.

!Output Panel Fields
  @Name            +- Storage Group Name
  @Type            +- The type of storage group (POOL/VIO/TAPE/OBJECT/OBJ-BACK)
  @Total           +- Total Space (in Mb) in the storage group
  @Free            +- Free Space (in Mb) available in the storage group
  @%Use            +- Used Space percentage
  @Hi              +- Migration threshold (high)
  @Low             +- Migration threshold (low)
  @Freq            +- Backup frequency
  @PSM             +- Is Primary Space Management active (PSM/No)
  @IMG             +- Is Interval Migration active (IMG/No)
  @AMG             +- Is Automatic Migration active (AMG/No)
  @BKP             +- Is Automatic Backup active (BKP/No)
  @DMP             +- Is Automatic Dump active (DMP/No)
+
+When only one storage group matches the specified pattern mask, a more detailed
+list is displayed. This is split into seven main sections. Values for some
+fields are only displayed if applicable to the type of storage group.

!Storage Group Attributes
  @Name            +- Storage Group Name
  @Type            +- The type of storage group (POOL/VIO/TAPE/OBJECT/OBJ-BACK)
  @Last Change Date+- The date (yyyy/mm/dd) of the last change
  @Last Change User+- The userid that performed the last change
  @Last Change Time+- The time (hh.mm.ss) of the last change
  @SMS Status      +- The SMS status of the Storage Group
  @Description     +- Description of the Storage Group

!Space Usage Information
  @Total Space (Mb)+- Total Space (in Mb) in the storage group
  @Percent Used    +- Used Space percentage
  @Free Space (Mb) +- Free Space (in Mb) available in the storage group
  @Online Volumes  +- Number of online volumes in the storage group
  @Offline Volumes +- Number of offline volumes in the storage group
+
!VIO Information
  @Maximum DSN Size+- Maximum size of a VIO dataset
  @Unit Type       +- The type of unit emulated for VIO allocations
+
!Migration Information
  @Auto-Migration  +- Automatic Migration status (Active/Inactive)
  @System          +- Automatic Migration system name
  @Intvl-Migration +- Interval Migration status (Active/Inactive)
  @Prim Space Mngmt+- Primary Space Management status (Active/Inactive)
  @High Threshold  +- Migration threshold (high)
  @Low Threshold   +- Migration threshold (low)
+
!Auto-Backup Information
  @Status          +- Automatic Backup status (Active/Inactive)
  @System          +- Automatic Backup system name
  @Frequency       +- Frequency of the backups
+
!Auto-Dump Information
  @Status          +- Automatic Dump status (Active/Inactive)
  @System          +- Automatic Dump system name
  @Classes         +- Dump Classes defined
+
!OAM Information
  @Table Space ID  +- OAM Table Space Group ID
  @Drive Start     +- Drive Start threshold
  @Cycle Start-End +- OAM Cycle start and end time (hh-hh)
  @Volume Full     +- Volume full threshold
  @Library Names   +- OAM Library Names available
+
!Volume Information
  @Volume Serial   +- The volume serial
  @SMS Status      +- The SMS Status of the volume
  @MVS Status      +- The MVS Status of the volume
  @Total Capacity  +- The total capacity (Mb) of the volume
  @Free            +- Total space free (Mb) on the volume
  @Largest Extent  +- Size (Mb) of the largest extent on the volume
  @Date            +- Date of last change to the volume definition
  @User            +- Userid who performed the last change
+
)INIT
.ATTRCHAR(¢)  = 'COLOR(&M7CC) HILITE(&M7CH) INTENS(&M7CI)'
.ATTRCHAR(!)  = 'COLOR(&M08C) HILITE(&M08H) INTENS(&M08I)'
.ATTRCHAR(+)  = 'COLOR(&M06C) HILITE(&M06H) INTENS(&M06I)'
.ATTRCHAR(@)  = 'COLOR(&M09C) HILITE(&M09H) INTENS(&M09I)'
)PROC
 &ZUP   = MXIHTOC
 &ZCONT = MXIHSMF
)END

MXIHSMF.text:
)PANEL KEYLIST (ISRHLP2 ISR)
)ATTR
  ¢ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(YELLOW)
  ! TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(WHITE)
  + TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
  @ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
  # AREA(SCRL) EXTEND(ON)
)BODY EXPAND(¯¯) DEFAULT($¦_)
¢MXI - HELP - SMF Command ------------------------------------------------------
!Option ===>_ZCMD
#MXIHAREA                                                                      #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
+
)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Displays the current SMF information
+
!Command Syntax
+ @SMF
+
!Output Panel Fields
+  The display is split into two sections
+
!SMF Configuration
  @System ID       +- System identifier
  @SMF Recording   +- SMF recording option
  @Job Wait Time   +- Time (hhmm) before IEFUTL is invoked
  @Max Dormancy    +- Maximum dormancy value
  @Interval        +- Default interval value
  @Sync            +- Default sync value
  @DD Consolidation+- Are DDNames to be consolidated
  @Status          +- Default status value
  @Member          +- The SMFPRMxx currently used
  @SMCA Address    +- The address of the SMCA control block
  @ASCB Address    +- The address of the ASCB control block for SMF
+
!SMF Subsystems
  @Interval        +- Interval value for this subsystem
  @Detail          +- Detail recording status for this subsystem
  @Subparm         +- The specified SUBPARM for this subsystem or 'n/a'
  @Types           +- Record types being recorded
  @Exits           +- Exits active for this subsystem
+
)INIT
.ATTRCHAR(¢)  = 'COLOR(&M7CC) HILITE(&M7CH) INTENS(&M7CI)'
.ATTRCHAR(!)  = 'COLOR(&M08C) HILITE(&M08H) INTENS(&M08I)'
.ATTRCHAR(+)  = 'COLOR(&M06C) HILITE(&M06H) INTENS(&M06I)'
.ATTRCHAR(@)  = 'COLOR(&M09C) HILITE(&M09H) INTENS(&M09I)'
)PROC
 &ZUP   = MXIHTOC
 &ZCONT = MXIHSMFD
)END

MXIHSSI.text:
)PANEL KEYLIST (ISRHLP2 ISR)
)ATTR
  ¢ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(YELLOW)
  ! TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(WHITE)
  + TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
  @ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
  # AREA(SCRL) EXTEND(ON)
)BODY EXPAND(¯¯) DEFAULT($¦_)
¢MXI - HELP - SSI Command ------------------------------------------------------
!Option ===>_ZCMD
#MXIHAREA                                                                      #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
+
)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Displays the current Subsystem entries. This command can be used to display
+  the active functions for subsystems that have correctly initialized their
+  subsystem vector table.
+
!Command Syntax
+ @SSI ssi-mask
+
!Keywords      +
  @ssi-mask    +An optional masking pattern that can be used to filter the
               +displayed list on all or part of the subsystem name.
               +The wildcard character of '*' and a placeholder character of '%'
               +can be used. The default value of ssi-mask is '*'.
+
!Example
+ @SSI DB*   +  - List all subsystems starting 'DB'
+
!Considerations
+  The data display has various formats depending on the amount of subsystems
+  to be displayed :
+  (a) All Subsystems
+  (b) Single Subsystem
+
!Output Panel Fields (Multiple Subsystems)
  @Name            +- Subsystem name in character format
  @Hex             +- Subsystem name in hex format
  @Status          +- Can subsystem process subsystem requests (Active/Inactive)
  @SSCT            +- Address of the subsystem control table
  @SSCTSUSE        +- Value in SSCTSUSE field (SSCT User 1)
  @SSCTSUS2        +- Value in SSCTSUS2 field (SSCT User 2)
  @SSVT            +- Address of the subsystem vector table
  @Dynamic         +- Is the subsystem dynamic?
  @SETSSI          +- Does the subsystem reject or accept SETSSI commands?
+
!Output Panel Fields (Single Subsystem)
  @Dec             +- Decimal subsystem request number
  @Hex             +- Hex subsystem request number
  @Description     +- Description of the subsystem request (if known)
  @EPA             +- Address of the function routine
  @Location        +- Storage location of the function routine
+
+  When the subsystem is active for SSI function 54, the following information
+  will also be shown :
+
!Subsystem Version Information
  @Name            +- The common name of the subsystem
  @FMID            +- The FMID of the subsystem software
  @Version         +- The version of the subsystem software
  @Product Level   +- The product level of the subsystem software
  @Service Level   +- The service level of the subsystem software
  @Variable Data   +- Any installation or system defined variable data
+
)INIT
.ATTRCHAR(¢)  = 'COLOR(&M7CC) HILITE(&M7CH) INTENS(&M7CI)'
.ATTRCHAR(!)  = 'COLOR(&M08C) HILITE(&M08H) INTENS(&M08I)'
.ATTRCHAR(+)  = 'COLOR(&M06C) HILITE(&M06H) INTENS(&M06I)'
.ATTRCHAR(@)  = 'COLOR(&M09C) HILITE(&M09H) INTENS(&M09I)'
)PROC
 &ZUP   = MXIHTOC
 &ZCONT = MXIHSTOR
)END

MXIHSTOR.text:
)PANEL KEYLIST (ISRHLP2 ISR)
)ATTR
  ¢ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(YELLOW)
  ! TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(WHITE)
  + TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
  @ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
  # AREA(SCRL) EXTEND(ON)
)BODY EXPAND(¯¯) DEFAULT($¦_)
¢MXI - HELP - STOR Command -----------------------------------------------------
!Option ===>_ZCMD
#MXIHAREA                                                                      #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
+
)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Displays the current system storage information
+
+  This command requires access to the ERBSMFI module supplied by RMF or CMF.
+
!Command Syntax
+ @STOR
+
!Output Panel Fields
+ The output values are divided into three main sections
+
!System Storage Values
  @Highest UIC     +- The highest value UIC detected
  @Central AFC     +- The Available Frame Count for Central Storage
  @Expanded Mig Age+- Expanded Storage migration age
  @Expanded AFC    +- The Available Frame Count for Expanded Storage
+
!Storage Residency Fields
  @Description     +- The storage area
  @Total           +- The total number of frames (if known)
  @Fixed           +- The number of fixed frames (if known)
  @Central         +- The number of central storage frames (if known)
  @Expanded        +- The number of expanded storage frames (if known)
+
!Paging Activity Fields
  @Description     +- The type of page activity
  @Direction       +- The direction of page movement
  @From            +- The source storage area
  @To              +- The target storage area
  @Number          +- The current rate (frames/pages per second)
+
)INIT
.ATTRCHAR(¢)  = 'COLOR(&M7CC) HILITE(&M7CH) INTENS(&M7CI)'
.ATTRCHAR(!)  = 'COLOR(&M08C) HILITE(&M08H) INTENS(&M08I)'
.ATTRCHAR(+)  = 'COLOR(&M06C) HILITE(&M06H) INTENS(&M06I)'
.ATTRCHAR(@)  = 'COLOR(&M09C) HILITE(&M09H) INTENS(&M09I)'
)PROC
 &ZUP   = MXIHTOC
 &ZCONT = MXIHSVC
)END

MXIHSVC.text:
)PANEL KEYLIST (ISRHLP2 ISR)
)ATTR
  ¢ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(YELLOW)
  ! TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(WHITE)
  + TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
  @ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
  # AREA(SCRL) EXTEND(ON)
)BODY EXPAND(¯¯) DEFAULT($¦_)
¢MXI - HELP - SVC Command ------------------------------------------------------
!Option ===>_ZCMD
#MXIHAREA                                                                      #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
+
)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Displays the current SVC table entries. This command can be used to display
+  the Extended SVC Router functions and SVC Update Recording Table entries.
+
!Command Syntax
+ @SVC num-mask
+
!Keywords      +
  @num-mask    +An optional decimal number that filters the displayed list by
               +all or part of the decimal SVC number.
               +The wildcard character of '*' and a placeholder character of '%'
               +can be used.
               +The default value for num-mask is '*'.
+
!Example
+ @SVC       +  - List all SVCs.
+ @SVC 23    +  - List SVC 23 Information.
+ @SVC 2%%   +  - List SVC 200-255.
+
!Considerations
+  The data display has various formats depending on the SVC number
+  chosen and the type of SVC:
+  (a) All SVCs
+  (b) Single SVC (with or without SVC Update Recording information)
+  (c) Extended Router SVC
+
!Output Panel Fields (Multiple SVCs)
  @Dec             +- Decimal SVC Number
  @Hex             +- Hexadecimal SVC Number
  @Module          +- SVC Module Name
  @Macro           +- Macro associated with the SVC
  @EPA             +- Entry point address of the module
  @Location        +- Storage location of the module
  @Typ             +- SVC Type (1,2,3/4,6)
  @APF             +- SVC requires APF authorisation
  @ESR             +- SVC is an Extended Router SVC
  @ASF             +- SVC uses SVC assist
  @AR              +- SVC can be issued in AR mode
  @UP              +- SVC has been updated
  @NP              +- SVC is non-preemptive
  @Locks           +- Locks required for SVC :
                     ¢L+: Local
                     ¢C+: Cross Memory Services (CMS)
                     ¢O+: Optimizer
                     ¢D+: Dispatcher
                     ¢S+: Space Alloc
+
!Output Panel Fields (Single SVC)
+The output is split into two sections
+
!Current SVC Information
  @Number (Dec)    +- Decimal SVC Number
  @SVC Type        +- SVC Type (1,2,3/4,6)
  @Number (Hex)    +- Hex SVC Number
  @Entry Point     +- Entry point address of the module
  @Location        +- Storage location of the module
  @Module Name     +- SVC Module Name
  @Macro  Name     +- Macro associated with the SVC
  @APF Authorized  +- SVC requires APF authorisation (Yes/No)
  @Non-Preemptive  +- SVC is non-preemptive (Yes/No)
  @AR Mode Capable +- SVC can be issued in AR mode (Yes/No)
  @Assisted        +- SVC uses SVC assist facility (Yes/No)
  @Locks Required  +- Locks required for SVC
+
!SVC Update Information
  @Update Count    +- Number of times SVC has been updated
  @Method          +- Last Method used to update the SVC
  @Date            +- Date of last update (yyyy/mm/dd)
  @Julian Date     +- Julian Date of last update (yyddd)
  @Old Entry Point +- Entry point address of the SVC prior to update
  @Location        +- Storage location of the SVC module prior to update
  @Old Module Name +- SVC Module Name prior to update
  @Type            +- SVC Type (1,2,3/4,6) prior to update
  @APF Authorized  +- SVC required APF authorisation (Yes/No)
  @Non-Preemptive  +- SVC was non-preemptive (Yes/No)
  @AR Mode Capable +- SVC could be issued in AR mode (Yes/No)
  @Assisted        +- SVC used SVC assist facility (Yes/No)
  @Locks Required  +- Locks required for SVC
+
!Output Panel Fields (Extended Router SVC)
  @Dec             +- Decimal SVC Function Code
  @Hex             +- Hex SVC Function Code
  @Module          +- SVC Function Module Name
  @EPA             +- Entry point address of the function module
  @Location        +- Storage location of the module
  @Type            +- SVC Type (1,2,3/4,6)
  @APF             +- SVC requires APF authorisation
  @ASF             +- SVC uses SVC assist
  @AR              +- SVC can be issued in AR mode
  @NP              +- SVC is non-preemptive
  @Locks           +- Locks required for SVC :
                     ¢L+: Local
                     ¢C+: Cross Memory Services (CMS)
                     ¢O+: Optimizer
                     ¢D+: Dispatcher
                     ¢S+: Space Alloc
+
)INIT
.ATTRCHAR(¢)  = 'COLOR(&M7CC) HILITE(&M7CH) INTENS(&M7CI)'
.ATTRCHAR(!)  = 'COLOR(&M08C) HILITE(&M08H) INTENS(&M08I)'
.ATTRCHAR(+)  = 'COLOR(&M06C) HILITE(&M06H) INTENS(&M06I)'
.ATTRCHAR(@)  = 'COLOR(&M09C) HILITE(&M09H) INTENS(&M09I)'
)PROC
 &ZUP   = MXIHTOC
 &ZCONT = MXIHSYM
)END

MXIHTAPE.text:
)PANEL KEYLIST (ISRHLP2 ISR)
)ATTR
  ¢ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(YELLOW)
  ! TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(WHITE)
  + TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
  @ TYPE(TEXT)    INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
  # AREA(SCRL) EXTEND(ON)
)BODY EXPAND(¯¯) DEFAULT($¦_)
¢MXI - HELP - TAPE Command -----------------------------------------------------
!Option ===>_ZCMD
#MXIHAREA                                                                      #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
#                                                                              #
+
)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Displays the current online TAPE units.
+
!Command Syntax
+ @TAPE unit-mask+
+
!Keywords      +
  @unit-mask   +An optional masking pattern that can be used to filter the
               +displayed list on all or part of the unit address.
               +The wildcard character of '*' and a placeholder character of '%'
               +can be used. The default value of unit-mask is '*'.
+
!Example
+ @TAPE 34*   + List all TAPE units in the range 0340-034F
+ @TAPE 590   + List TAPE unit 590
+
!Considerations
+ If the resultant list from the TAPE command contains only a single entry,
+ a more detailed panel is displayed.
+
!Output Panel Fields (Multiple Tape Units)
  @Unit            +- Device unit address
  @Status          +- Status of the device
  @Type            +- Device type of the unit
  @Volser          +- Volume serial number mounted on the unit
  @Label           +- Label Number being processed
  @LTyp            +- Type of label being used
  @Jobname         +- Name of job using the device
  @EXCP            +- Number of I/Os performed to this device. Note that for
                   +  24-bit UCBs this value is taken from the UCBSIO field
                   +  which is a halfword and will wrap every 65K I/Os. For
                   +  31-bit UCBs, the value is taken from UCBCX-SIO which
                   +  is a fullword.
  @BLP             +- Bypass Label Processing status
  @IDRC            +- Hardware Compression status
+
!Output Panel Fields (Single Tape Unit)
+The display is split into five sections
+
!Unit Information
  @Device Address   +- Device unit address
  @Device Type      +- Device type of the unit
  @Ready            +- Is the unit ready (Yes/No)
  @Allocated        +- Is the unit being used (Yes/No)
  @Rewinding        +- Is the unit rewinding (Yes/No)
  @Unloading        +- Is the unit unloading (Yes/No)
  @Overall Status   +- Status of the device
  @Unloading        +- Is the unit unloading (Yes/No)
  @Intervention     +- Does the device require intervention (Yes/No)
  @UCB Address      +- Address of the real UCB
  @Unitnames        +- EDT unitnames that this device is defined to
+
!Error Recording Information
  @Temporary Read   +- Number of temporary read errors encountered
  @Permanent Read   +- Number of permanent read errors encountered
  @Temporary Write  +- Number of temporary write errors encountered
  @Permanent Write  +- Number of permanent write errors encountered
  @Noise Blocks     +- Number of noise blocks encountered
  @Erase Gaps       +- Number of erase gaps encountered
+
!Active Tape Information
  @Volume Serial    +- Volume Serial of mounted tape
  @BLP              +- Bypass Label Processing active (Yes/No)
  @IDRC             +- Hardware Compression active (Yes/No)
  @Job Using Tape   +- Name of job using the device
  @Label Number     +- Label Number being processed
  @Label Type       +- Type of label being used
  @I/O Count        +- Number of I/Os performed to this device. Note that for
                    +  24-bit UCBs this value is taken from the UCBSIO field
                    +  which is a halfword and will wrap every 65K I/Os. For
                    +  31-bit UCBs, the value is taken from UCBCX-SIO which
                    +  is a fullword.
+
!Configuration Data Records ¢(*)
  @Device Type      +- The device type
  @Device Serial    +- The device serial number
  @Cntl Unit Type   +- The control unit type
  @Cntl Unit Serial +- The control unit serial number
+
+               ¢(*)+- Only available when MXI is running authorized.
+
!Channel Connections
  @CHPid            +- Channel Path ID
  @Channel Path Type+- Type of channel path
  @Status           +- Status of the channel path
+
)INIT
